Top seed Novak Djokovic saved a match point on Sunday before defeating Sebastian Korda to win Adelaide International and reinforce his status as a heavy title favourite for the Australian Open. The 21-time Grand Slam winner needed more than three hours to stamp his authority on his unseeded American opponent, son of former world No 2 Petr Korda, 6-7 (8/10), 7-6 (7/3), 6-4. In doing so, Djokovic extended his unbeaten streak in Australia to 34 straight matches and won his fifth consecutive final dating to Tel Aviv last year. The winner of 92 career titles now heads to the Australian Open in about a week with momentum.